  "title": "SeizeIT2",
  "description": "SeizeIT2 is a multicenter prospective study validating wearable EEG (Sensor Dot device) in adult and pediatric patients with refractory epilepsy. The dataset comprises 125 patients from 5 European epilepsy monitoring units, containing approximately 11,640 hours of simultaneous wearable EEG, ECG, EMG, and movement data with 886 annotated focal seizure events recorded during presurgical evaluation.",
  "methods_description": "Participants with refractory epilepsy admitted for long-term video-EEG monitoring were recorded simultaneously with the Sensor Dot wearable device. The device recorded EEG at 250 Hz from electrodes placed on the mastoid region, ECG and EMG from chest and deltoid placements, and movement data (accelerometers and gyroscopes) at 25 Hz. EEG electrode placement followed the 10-20 system or 25-electrode array based on suspected seizure onset location.",
